0\lt x\lt 1
E(X^2)
\sum_{x\in\omega}x^2P(x)\lt \infty
\forall x \le 0:\space \sum_{x\in\omega}xP(x) \le \sum_{x\in\omega}x^2P(x) = E(X^2)\lt \infty \\  \forall x\ge 1:\space \sum_{x\in\omega}xP(x) \le \sum_{x\in\omega}x^2P(x) = E(X^2)\lt \infty
|x|< 1+x^2
x \in \mathbb R
E[|X|] < 1+E[X^2] < \infty
E[X]
E(X)
\int|x|  f_X(x) \, dx < \infty
\int_{|x|\le1}  |x|f_X(x) \, dx + \int_{|x|>1} |x| f_X(x) \, dx \le\\\le \int_{|x|\le1}  f_X(x) \, dx + \int_{|x|>1} x^2 f_X(x) \, dx \le \\  \le 1 + E(X^2) \le \infty 
